author: stefan2
msg: Fix a major latency snafu in svnserve.  Sequences of small requests
and responses would be delayed in the TCP/IP stack by Nagle's alogrithm.
That becomes obvious when e.g. running "ls -R".
(svn_ra_svn_create_conn3): send data as soon as write copy it from
our send buffers to the socket

author: desruisseaux
msg: Renamed getAffineTransform() as getPositionVectorTransformation(), which is a more accurate description of what this method is computing.
The corresponding EPSG operation method is 1033.
